{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory allocation bug in database_get_ids and database_get_groups\n\n### Summary\nThere's a bug in the tracer database functions `database_get_ids` and `database_get_groups` where they allocate 8 times more memory than needed on 64-bit systems. This causes memory corruption that can affect the behavior of other functions including `number_of_ids()`.\n\nThe issue occurs because the code uses `sizeof(char **)` instead of `sizeof(char *)` when allocating memory for arrays of strings. On 64-bit systems, this results in allocating 8 bytes per pointer instead of 4 bytes, leading to buffer overruns and memory corruption.\n\nThis can cause segmentation faults, incorrect return values from `number_of_ids()`, and other undefined behavior when the tracer database is used.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/database.c`: \n  - Line 486: Changed `sizeof(char **)` to `sizeof(char *)` in `database_get_ids`\n  - Line 495: Changed `sizeof(char **)` to `sizeof(char *)` in `database_get_groups`\n\n"
}